    "body": "## Purpose\n\nCreative/product foundation for Stage 6 Step 9 before Codex implementation.\n\nThis PR is deliberately **draft** and **documentation/data only**. It does not modify runtime/game code and is not frozen implementation authority.\n\n## Authority\n\nBaseline main: `7673f3487b0dd52c0c5cb2c7826f4e3fe5cc570e`.\n\nStep 9 target: five unmistakable Russian-first generation voices built from one invariant semantic intent per row:\n\n`Boomer / Gen X / Millennial / Zoomer / Alpha`\n\nRule: `NO FALSE OR MISUSED SLANG`, not `NO SLANG`.\n\n## Key findings\n\n### Gen X is unfinished, not nonexistent\n\nCurrent runtime already has birth-year routing `1965-1980 -> genX` and canonical `genx -> genX` normalization, but supported registry/text mode/dictionaries/presentation/smoke coverage do not make it first-class.\n\n### Historical profile collapse is measurable\n\nSeed inventory snapshot (`e94e4bcb...`, 2026-07-03) contains 57 resolved core keys with all four old player profiles:\n- `Zoomer == Alpha`: **57 / 57**\n- `Boomer == Millennial`: **19 / 57**\n\nThis directly explains the user's visual report that Zoomer and Alpha did not feel distinct.\n\n### Seed inventory scope\n\nHistorical seed package:\n- 1930 active records\n- 853 unique active texts\n- 306 dynamic templates\n\nIt is older than current main and is seed/forensic evidence only. Fresh current-main inventory rebuild is required before freeze.\n\n## Current foundation artifacts\n\n1. `STAGE6_STEP9_FIVE_PROFILE_FOUNDATION.md`\n2. `STAGE6_STEP9_CREATIVE_REVIEW_INDEX.md`\n3. `STAGE6_STEP9_FIVE_PROFILE_RU_VOICE_BIBLES_DRAFT.md`\n4. `STAGE6_STEP9_GENX_PROFILE_DRAFT.md`\n5. `STAGE6_STEP9_LEGACY_COPY_RECOVERY_AUDIT.md`\n6. `STAGE6_STEP9_FULL_TEXT_INVENTORY_COVERAGE_PLAN.md`\n7. `STAGE6_STEP9_RU_SEMANTIC_MATRIX_DRAFT.md` - Batch 1, first 48 high-frequency intents\n8. `STAGE6_STEP9_RU_SEMANTIC_MATRIX_BATCH2_DRAFT.md` - events, vote, economy, REP, cop/report, reactions\n9. `STAGE6_STEP9_RU_SEMANTIC_MATRIX_BATCH3_SYSTEM_EVENTS_DRAFT.md` - movement/feed/battle/robbery/unlocks/system wrappers\n10. `STAGE6_STEP9_RU_SEMANTIC_MATRIX_BATCH4_CONFLICT_ECONOMY_DRAFT.md` - rematch, tactical costs, reroll, hints, extra vote, vote shield, intervention, NPC events, dismiss, respect, reports, voting economy\n11. `STAGE6_STEP9_START_ONBOARDING_FIVE_PROFILE_DRAFT.md`\n12. `STAGE6_STEP9_NPC_FIVE_PROFILE_VOICE_PACK_DRAFT.md` - bandit/toxic/cop/crowd/mafia\n13. `STAGE6_STEP9_SLANG_SEMANTIC_VALIDATION.md`\n14. `STAGE6_STEP9_CODEX_IMPLEMENTATION_CONTRACT.md`\n15. `stage6_step9_ru_semantic_matrix_draft.json`\n\n## Slang semantic gate\n\nCreative review already rejects known misuse rather than maximizing slang blindly:\n- `fanum tax 💰` as generic money robbery: reject, wrong semantic context;\n- `skill issue` as generic bandit compliance threat: reject;\n- generic `sigma mode` for start: too vague/forced;\n- `rizz` as generic REP/influence: reject unless actual charm/flirt semantics;\n- `skibidi` as stable synonym for `bad`: reject.\n\nStrong generation voice is required, but semantic correctness outranks token cosplay.\n\n## Conflict/economy safety\n\nBatch 4 explicitly locks mechanics:\n- costs and dynamic values remain source-driven;\n- payer/receiver semantics cannot change;\n- REP/points/influence math cannot change;\n- rematch keeps canonical payer/cost-growth/no-direct-REP behavior;\n- voting economy remains canonical;\n- target REP must never be shown as player REP;\n- unified PR #258 stat-toast coalescing stays intact.\n\n## Codex boundary\n\nCodex must not implement any DRAFT copy.\n\nImplementation begins only after User + ChatGPT create and explicitly approve a frozen exact mapping/hash. Codex then consumes exact copy and must not invent, soften, sanitize, translate, shorten, or substitute synonyms.\n\n## Current diff\n\nBranch: `chatgpt/stage6-step9-five-profile-foundation-20260723`\n\nCurrent head: `3099eb6ec4e584a9aa16ff95644c7aca1a1329f5`\n\nCompared with baseline main:\n- 15 commits ahead\n- 0 behind\n- exactly 15 added documentation/data files\n- no runtime/game files changed\n\n`ai-forensics-evidence` run `374`: success.\n\n## Status\n\n`STAGE 6: NOT COMPLETE`\n\n`STEP 9: FOUNDATION_IN_PROGRESS / NOT_FROZEN`\n\nNext action: continue creative review/expansion, rebuild fresh current-main inventory before freeze, then produce exact frozen five-profile mapping/hash for Codex.",
